Class AsearchNode<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • AsearchNode<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - Object held within this node
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    SearchNode<E>

    public class AsearchNode<E>
extends java.lang.Object
implements SearchNode<E>
    Acts as a node that operates in an A* search. This acts as a state space by storing all previous nodes that have been visited upon reaching the current AsearchNode.

    A single object is contained within each node.
    Author:
    Hayden Charles Smith, z3418003
    Last modified: 19th May 2013
